FuncDef: This command sets the power priority value for the 7950 XRS.

ParaDef.Info: Specifies the power priority level. An operator must assign a priority value to each XMA using a range of number from 1 to 200. The lowest number has the highest priority. The priority number range from 1 to 100 should be used for modules considered essential for system operation. Lower priority values of 101 to 200 should be used for non-essential modules.
